## Current Status

# Active Directory Enterprise Lab

## Project Overview

This project demonstrates the deployment and administration of a Windows Server 2022 Active Directory environment designed to simulate an enterprise Windows domain. The lab focuses on identity management, Group Policy, Windows authentication, security auditing, and basic enterprise networking.

---

## Technologies Used

- Windows Server 2022
- Windows 11
- Active Directory Domain Services
- DNS
- Group Policy
- PowerShell
- Oracle VirtualBox
- Sysmon
- Windows Event Viewer

---

# Lab Walkthrough

## 1. Domain Join

Successfully joined a Windows 11 workstation (CLIENT0011) to the **corp.local** Active Directory domain.

![Domain Join](Images/CLIENT0011 successfully joined corp.local domain.png)

---

## 2. Computer Account Created in Active Directory

After joining the domain, the workstation was automatically added to Active Directory Users and Computers.

This demonstrates successful communication between the client and the domain controller.

![Computer Account](Images/Client0011 under workstations in corp.local.png)

---

## 3. Organizational Unit Management

Created a dedicated **Workstations** Organizational Unit and moved CLIENT0011 into it to better organize domain computers and prepare for Group Policy deployment.

![Workstations OU](Images/CLIENT0011 moved to workstations.png)

---

## 4. Group Policy Deployment

Created and linked a workstation security Group Policy Object (GPO).

This policy was applied to computers inside the Workstations Organizational Unit.

![GPO Linked](Images/DC01 workstation security policy 03-10-26.png)

---

## 5. Account Lockout Policy

Configured account lockout settings including:

- Lockout Threshold
- Lockout Duration
- Reset Counter After

These policies simulate enterprise account security practices.

![Account Lockout Policy](Images/account group policy settings 03-10.png)

---

## 6. Advanced Audit Policy

Configured Windows Advanced Audit Policies to record successful and failed credential validation events.

This provides visibility into authentication activity.

![Audit Policy](Images/audit credential validation for DC01.png)

---

## 7. Failed Authentication (Event ID 4625)

Generated failed login attempts to create Windows Security Event ID **4625**.

This event can be used by administrators and security analysts to investigate failed authentication attempts.

![4625 Event](Images/event 4625 client0011.png)

---

## 8. Authentication Details

Reviewed Event Viewer logs to identify:

- Source Workstation
- Source IP Address
- Logon Type
- Failure Status Codes

This information is commonly used during security investigations.

![Authentication Details](Images/CLIENT0011 log 4625 evidence of login failure 03-16-26.png)

---

## 9. Account Lockout Event (4740)

Triggered an account lockout after repeated failed logon attempts.

Verified Event ID **4740** was successfully logged.

![4740 Event](Images/event 4740, logout notification successful 03-10-26.png)

---

## 10. Domain Authentication Verification

Verified successful authentication by logging into the domain and confirming the logged-on user with PowerShell.

```
whoami
```

Output:

```
corp\labuser
```

![Whoami](Images/corp-labuser verified.png)

---

## 11. Network Connectivity Testing

Validated communication between the Windows client and Domain Controller using ICMP.

```
ping 192.168.56.10
```

Successful responses confirmed proper network connectivity.

![Ping Test](Images/successful ping to domain controller.png)

---

## 12. Sysmon Deployment

Installed Microsoft Sysmon to enhance endpoint logging for future security monitoring and SIEM integration.

Verified the Sysmon service was successfully installed and running.

![Sysmon](Images/Sysmon installed on Client01 successfully 04-27-26.png)

---

